# PLACEHOLDER — minisign public key for MARVIN release signing
#
# This file is referenced by .github/workflows/release.yml (in the
# release-notes template's verify recipe) and by docs/decisions/0026-
# release-artefact-signing-minisign.md. Until the actual key is
# generated and uploaded, releases skip the signing step gracefully.
#
# Replacement procedure (one-time):
#   1. brew install minisign
#   2. minisign -G -p ~/.minisign/marvin.pub -s ~/.minisign/marvin.key
#      (choose a strong password; store it in a password manager)
#   3. cat ~/.minisign/marvin.pub
#      — it has two lines: a comment + the base64-encoded pubkey.
#   4. Replace this entire file's content with those two lines.
#   5. gh secret set MINISIGN_SECRET_KEY --repo RobertIlisei/MARVIN \
#        --body "$(cat ~/.minisign/marvin.key)"
#      gh secret set MINISIGN_PASSWORD --repo RobertIlisei/MARVIN \
#        --body '<the-password>'
#   6. Commit the updated `.minisign-pubkey` file.
#   7. Cut the next release (v0.1.x); the workflow signs the zip and
#      uploads a .minisig sidecar.
#
# See ADR-0026 §"Key generation + secret-store onboarding" for full
# context including the rotation policy.
